## Task 2: The "Distant Horizons" LOD System

### Objective
Design an LOD Management System that supports massive view distances by using simplified chunk representations beyond the active radius.

### Implementation Requirements

#### 2.1 LOD Management System
- **Active Radius**: Full 16x256x16 chunk arrays only within "Active Radius" (Phase 10 view distance)
- **Beyond Active Radius**: Use simplified chunk representations
- **Reference**: [LODLevel.java](mdc:src/main/java/me/alextzamalis/graphics/LODLevel.java) already defines LOD levels but needs integration

#### 2.2 SimplifiedChunk / SuperChunk Data Structure
- **Create SimplifiedChunk or SuperChunk** data structure
- **Downsampled representation**: 1 block represents a 4x4 area (or configurable)
- **Memory efficient**: Store only visible "shell" blocks, not internal hidden blocks
- **Serialization**: Efficient serialization for disk storage
- **Transition zones**: Smooth transitions between full chunks and simplified chunks

#### 2.3 Shader-Level LOD Transitions
- **Prevent "pop-in"** visual artifacts
- **Z-fighting prevention**: Use depth bias or offset for LOD transitions
- **Alpha-dither fading**: Optional shader-based dithering for smooth LOD transitions
- **Distance-based blending**: Blend between high-detail and low-detail meshes

### Files to Modify/Create
- `src/main/java/me/alextzamalis/voxel/SimplifiedChunk.java` (NEW)
- `src/main/java/me/alextzamalis/voxel/SuperChunk.java` (NEW - alternative name)
- `src/main/java/me/alextzamalis/voxel/LODManager.java` (NEW)
- `src/main/java/me/alextzamalis/voxel/AsyncChunkManager.java` (UPDATE to support LOD)
- `src/main/resources/assets/shaders/fragment.glsl` (UPDATE for LOD transitions)

