## Why This Approach Works

### MDI (Multi-Draw Indirect)
- **Single biggest "Sodium" upgrade**: Moves draw call logic from CPU to GPU
- **Performance**: Instead of 500 calls to draw 500 chunks, you make one
- **Reduces CPU overhead**: Less driver overhead, better GPU utilization

### Hytale Pattern System
- **Minecraft v1 generation**: Just "Math + Random"
- **Hytale v2 generation**: Uses "Logic + Prefabs"
- **Heuristic Placement Engine**: Checks the world before decorating it
- **Result**: More interesting, curated worlds instead of pure noise-based terrain

### Distant Horizons (LOD)
- **Key isn't just "drawing smaller things"**: It's managing data memory
- **SuperChunk serializer**: Strips out all hidden blocks, only saves "shell" for horizon
- **Memory efficient**: Allows massive view distances without memory explosion

